cs.umass.edu.myactivitiestoolkit.view.fragments

Class LocationsFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • Fragment
      • cs.umass.edu.myactivitiestoolkit.view.fragments.LocationsFragment

  • public class LocationsFragment
extends Fragment
    Fragment which visualizes the stored locations along with their clusters and allows the user to select a clustering algorithm and change its parameters. The locations are visualized using Google Maps API.

    Assignment 5 : Before you get started, you will need a Google API key. See the assignment details for instructions on how to do this. You will be implementing several clustering algorithms:
    1. You will implement DBScan for generic-typed Clusterable points. See DBScan.
    2. You will cluster locations using k-means in scikit-learn
    3. You will cluster locations using mean-shift in scikit-learn


    In this file, you will be implementing runDBScan(GPSLocation[], float, int), runKMeans(GPSLocation[], int), runMeanShift(GPSLocation[]) and drawClusters(Collection).
    See Also:
    GoogleMap, MapView, LocationService, Fragment, DBScan, Clusterable, Cluster, ClusteringRequest

        public void onStart()
        When the fragment starts, register a receiver to receive messages from the LocationService. The intent filter defines messages we are interested in receiving. We would like to receive notifications for when the service has started and stopped in order to update the toggle icon appropriately.
